      • processServerConfiguration

        public static List<DataAccessPoint> processServerConfiguration(Model configuration,
                                                               Context context)
        Process a configuration file and return the DataAccessPoints; set the context provided for server-wide settings. This bundles together the steps:
        • findServer(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model)
        • parseContext(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Resource)
        • processLoadClass(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Resource) (legacy)
        • servicesAndDatasets(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model)

      • processServerConfiguration

        • findServer(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model)
        • parseContext(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Resource)
        • processLoadClass(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Resource) (legacy)

      • servicesAndDatasets

        public static List<DataAccessPoint> servicesAndDatasets(Model model)
        Find and process datasets and services in a configuration file. This can be a Fuseki server configuration file or a services-only configuration file. It looks fuseki:services ( .... ) then, if not found, all rtdf:type fuseki:services.
        See Also:
        processServerConfiguration(org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model, org.apache.jena.sparql.util.Context)

      • servicesAndDatasets

        public static List<DataAccessPoint> servicesAndDatasets(Resource server)
        Find and process datasets and services in a configuration file starting from server which can have a fuseki:services ( .... ) but, if not found, all rdf:type fuseki:services are processed.
